208
00:16:20,352 --> 00:16:22,333
were, the first was new designers.

209
00:16:22,414 --> 00:16:26,656
This was a section in the exhibition which is perhaps a slightly more traditional approach

210
00:16:26,676 --> 00:16:30,318
to the way that the V&A would normally display design disciplines.

211
00:16:30,819 --> 00:16:35,041
It was a space where we looked into the design discipline or the design practice of eight

212
00:16:35,182 --> 00:16:36,943
key contemporary video games.

213
00:16:37,423 --> 00:16:43,927
It was a very eclectic range of games that were sort of from different genres, that were

214
00:16:43,987 --> 00:16:49,691
from designers of different scales, so from big AAA blockbusters to small independent studios.

215
00:16:50,792 --> 00:16:56,375
They were games which all had different design ambitions, but the thing that unites every single

216
00:16:56,555 --> 00:17:00,838
game within this section, every single game in the whole exhibition, is that they're breaking

217
00:17:01,559 --> 00:17:04,421
They're breaking new ground in some way, that they are groundbreaking,

218
00:17:04,481 --> 00:17:08,944
they're pushing our expectations of what video games are or what they can be in new ways.

219
00:17:10,145 --> 00:17:14,109
In Disruptors, the second section, we looked at the social and political conversations that

