00:17:14,149 --> 00:17:18,993
surround video games and understanding that if we're to really appreciate and respect video games

221
00:17:19,193 --> 00:17:23,636
as a contemporary design discipline, we need to have the same critical and nuanced conversations

222
00:17:23,696 --> 00:17:27,019
about that discipline as we do any other creative field or medium.

223
00:17:27,955 --> 00:17:31,838
And the last section of the exhibition was sort of split into two halves.

224
00:17:31,858 --> 00:17:34,761
And this is where we were looking at video games from the perspective of the player

225
00:17:35,341 --> 00:17:41,806
and understanding that actually no story or no perspective on contemporary design in video games is complete

226
00:17:41,826 --> 00:17:47,111
without also acknowledging or appreciating the design stories of the player

