00:21:05,266 --> 00:21:05,286
a— . . . . . . . . . . . .

282
00:21:06,346 --> 00:21:12,851
strong issues of a physical scale that show us why architecture is a complex medium to

283
00:21:12,891 --> 00:21:17,014
bring into a museum, that you can't necessarily display many buildings inside another building.

284
00:21:17,435 --> 00:21:20,897
And so instead this is a field that's had to work to identify different objects and

285
00:21:20,937 --> 00:21:25,381
materials and artifacts that can be brought into an exhibition space that help to present

286
00:21:25,421 --> 00:21:28,223
to a visitor and show that as a designed object.

287
00:21:29,392 --> 00:21:33,376
And so we spoke with these different designers to get them to show this materiality of this

288
00:21:33,436 --> 00:21:35,698
debris that existed from their design process.

